body_html:
@martinwicke , In answer to the question, "However, many (maybe most) actual models have several outputs. What should happen in this case?"

For models with several outputs, you would probably want to follow the way other scikit-learn models handle this. If you are going for scikit-learn compatibility.

http://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.multioutput.MultiOutputRegressor.html

Also, it seems like SKFLOW/TFLearn currently does not support models with more than one output (for regression). Please see #6849
